dict.string:
## Usage


Your Xcode project should reside in **[your Xojo project folder]/Xcode/___PACKAGENAME___**    



Next, add a **build script** to the Xojo project, active for **release**.

```
//sets XOJO_BUILD_LOCATION for the Xcode project scripts  
dim setAppPath as string = "export XOJO_BUILD_LOCATION="""+CurrentBuildLocationNative+"/___PACKAGENAME___.app"";"  
//cd Xcode to the folder where the xcodeproj file lives  
dim cdProjectPath as string = "cd  ""$PROJECT_PATH"+"/Xcode/___PACKAGENAME___"";"    

//clean any previous build  
call doshellcommand(setAppPath + cdProjectPath + " xcodebuild clean -scheme ___PACKAGENAME___ > build_log.txt 2>&1")  
//do the work  
call doshellcommand(setAppPath + cdProjectPath + " xcodebuild -scheme ___PACKAGENAME___ >> build_log.txt 2>&1")  
//Add to Xcode Organizer  
call doshellcommand(setAppPath + cdProjectPath + "xcodebuild archive -scheme ___PACKAGENAME___ >> build_log.txt 2>&1")    
```
